@NODE "Mail_8" "3d stuff..."
From: Stephen Fellner <sfell@xtra.co.nz>
Date: Sat, 10 Oct 1998 19:40:03 +1200
Subject: 3d stuff...

Hi all !

I've heard somebody asking about 3d stuff in blitz...

Well, the advantage of using polar coordinates is that rotation becomes dead
easy. But plotting becomes somewhat slower, as your polar coordinates must be
converted into rectangular before you can do the 3D plotting. However, there's
a way to rotate points in 3D, directly in rectangular without having to
convert back-forth from polar. Although I only have the formulas for 2D
rotation at the moment, it shouldn't be very difficult to extend them to 3d...

I've written a program that plots a 3D torus that you can move around the
screen... only wireframe at the moment, no fancy phong shading etc, but it's
still nice :)

Cheers,
Stephen



@ENDNODE
