@NODE "Mail_21" "Re: Anim from disk"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Sun, 25 Oct 1998 18:16:31 +0000
From: "Nick Chapman" <scillo@geocities.com>
Subject: Re: Anim from disk
Date: Thu, 22 Oct 1998 16:55:01 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit

AmiCartoon is a utility from Skillo which will come out early in 1999. It
is, quite simply, MovieSetter for the new millenium. As the name suggests,
it is best suited to making cartoons or introductory animations for games.
It will be a (cheap) commerical title that comes with a freely distributable
player. It will work on a frame-by-frame basis, and sound can be added to
each frame. It will extremely easy to use, but, obviously, useless for
animations that require the whole background to change. Since it is
programmed in Blitz, it will use the Blitz shape format. This means that
Blitz users will have added flexibility since they can use the RedShapeZ to
feed AmiCartoon with the data it needs.

Nick / Skillo

-----Original Message-----
