@NODE "Mail_26" "Re: asl screen requestor"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Thu, 08 Oct 1998 17:11:35 -0500
Subject: Re: asl screen requestor

Hi Steven,

On 05-Oct-98, S.J.CROY wrote:
> Hi all
>     I was wondering if it was possible to get the workbench 
> screen to appear in the asl-screen request command.  I`m using 
> the one built into blitz.  Am I going to have to call the function by 
> myself?

I think you are confusing the AslScreenRequest command.  This is not a listing
of available public screens.  It is for letting you select from a listing of
available screenmodes and sizes, such as Pal lo-res, NTSC hi-res-laced, etc. 
Then you make your own custom screen using this information.

If you want to choose among the current public screens that are already open,
you will need to code this yourself.


                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




