@NODE "Mail_28" "Re: bad tokens.."
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Wed, 7 Oct 1998 02:12:54 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Wed, 07 Oct 1998 01:42:24 +0000
Subject: Re: bad tokens..

Hi,

> Heya .. this is mainly diercted at Paul Burkey since it came from his e-mail
> test code.. but I figured I'd throw it out to the list to see if anyone else
> can guess it.. since it's probly so old he doesn't recognise the code.. ;)

> If ?????(1,"t:AnonMail.tmp")=False Then End

Ahh, that should be:

If AddNotify(1,"t:AnonMail.tmp")=False Then End

> the main stumper is this.. 
> If ?????=1 Then Gosub grab ; check if email changed since last timel

This should be:

If CheckNotify=1 Then Gosub grab

Both commands are from the RI Dos Lib which is part of the Blitz
Support Suite. At the time when I wrote that AnonMail program it
looked like everyone had bought BSS so it wasn't such a big deal
to use it in example code. Now we see a lot of new Blitz users
and BSS doesn't seem to be as widely used. 

The commands basicly add a "notify" check to the file an if the
file changes (Text file has been edited...) The program would
grab the new Subject: From: To: etc.. into the GUI of the Emailer.

All that stuff can be done with AmigaOS but I don't hve any
examples. So, you should either get BSS yourself or read through
the Autodocs for the free way to do it! :)

Cheers,

-- 
Paul Burkey <--> http://burkey.home.ml.org <-->



