@NODE "Mail_32" "Re: BitmapToWindow"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Wed, 21 Oct 1998 10:58:36 -0500
Subject: Re: BitmapToWindow

Hi Steven,

On 21-Oct-98, S.J.CROY wrote:
> 
> Hello all..
>     Has anyone had any luck changing the jam mode for 
> BitmapToWindow?.  I`ve tried the usual WJam command, but I 
> think this only works for text :((( I`ve looked through the autodoc`s 
> and haven`t really found anything that will help me.  

BitMapToWindow only copies the bitmap to the window as-is.  Any alterations to
the bitmap must be done first. 

If you are trying to combine the bitmap with what is already in the window,
you might try using a shape instead of a bitmap.  You can use "ShapesBitMap"
to allow you to use BitMap drawing commands on the shape, if needed.
  
Then use the BlitMode commands and Wblit for the copy.


                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




