> Well blitter can do it very easily, but Blitz support for it isn't very
> clear to me, so I don't know how it could be done, but you can use the OS
> blitting routines. So get a copy of RKRMs and look Graphics library
> routines, and I think you will find what you nead.
> 
> minterm is something like this, if I remember correctly the bolean
> operations:
> 
> Uppercase -> Logical NOT performed to the channel source.
> +         -> Logical OR preformed between left and right side.
> No space  -> Logical AND between channels.
> 
> d=Abc+AbC+aBc+aBC
> 
> the combination of Abc+AbC will ignorre the channel C completely.
> The other channels are Source A and B and the destination D.
> 
> Source A should be the bitmap which is copien to the destination D
> and the source B should point to the Destination bitmap as well.
> 
> This will eXlusive OR the source to the destination, and if performed
> twice will return the original image.
> 
> If you didn't understand everything then just mail me and I can try to be
> more understandable if possible. ;)
> 

