  Do we use tokenisation for the source code? If we just use ASCII we
don't have to worry about lib clashes, as the lib numbers are set each
time deflibs is made. As the machines will be fast, it won't be slow to
load in the ASCII.  =

  As the new machines will have fast CPU's, games will be OS legal-
which means it's easy to have game routines, as all you have to do is
call shared libraries (RTG, RTA) etc. =

  I was thinking we could also try writing an assembler coverter, like =

68k to PPC, as the CISC codes should be easy to emulate with RISC ones.
then things like the control routines data lib could be easily converted
to another CPU- the deflibs may be harder or not feasible, but it's
