@NODE "Mail_53" "Re: Blitz PPC"
From: Rick Hodger <rick.thehub@bigfoot.com>
Date: Fri, 09 Oct 1998 10:35:35 +0000
Organization: Corrupted Software
Subject: Re: Blitz PPC

I watched as Anton Reinauer hammered "Re: Blitz PPC" out on their
keyboard...

AR>   Yes, that's a good point- it's confusing having a different
syntax
AR> for Commands and Functions- but I like having the [] which stops
the
AR> Function/Command being confused with arrays. I think E uses the []
for
AR> Functions. And the [] are easier to type in than {} or ()  :)

But the "[]" is already used as well in arrays:

NEWTYPE.mynewtype
    init.b
    string$[4]
End NEWTYPE

etc.

AR>   Yes, if it's done like the rest of your libs- it would produce
very
AR> small programs :-) And if we just compiled in the actual functions
AR> needed, rather than the whole lib, it would make things really
small!
AR> Especially if Amiga Int uses Amiga OS in Palm-tops, and WebTVs,
small
AR> efficient programs will piss all over Windows CE :-) 

As long as it can optimise for different processors, as that's
something that seriously lacks in the current version.

AR>  Do we use tokenisation for the source code? If we just use ASCII
we
AR> don't have to worry about lib clashes, as the lib numbers are set
each
AR> time deflibs is made. As the machines will be fast, it won't be
slow to
AR> load in the ASCII.  

We've had this conversation before, the built in editor should use
tokenisation, but it should save the files in ASCII so that other
editors can be used if people want to (eg. GoldEd).  It'll make
loading slower, but better overall.

AR>  Yep, just give me some time- don't worry I don't forget things
like
AR> this- I won't lose interest because it's been a couple of months

AR>  We'll have to think of the name some time, as I don't know if
we'll
AR> get away with using a name with Blitz in it- we might be lucky and
can,
AR> I don't know. 

I still think you should go and speak to Amiga Inc., they might be
interested in supporting such a project.

See ya later!
-- 
