 by mail.enterprise.net (8.8.5/8.8.5) with ESMTP id QAA12456 for
 <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>; Sat, 17 Oct 1998 16:02:51 +0100 (GMT/BST)
Date: Sat, 17 Oct 1998 15:50:26 +0000
From: Matthew Parsons <billyray@enterprise.net>
Subject: Re: Blitz PPC
Organization: Private User
encoding: 7bit

WHY WHY WHY WHY WHY WHY WHY WHY  are we disscussing names?

We are all (most of us) competant coders, so insted of moaning that
you prefer the name BeerBasic over Magma (a personal fave of mine),
lets start to define how to construct this new system.

Here is my idea:
Lets build a macro assembler.
Build a simple core set of macro instructions, that use the assembler
        language of the assembler. 
Then build a large set of macro libraries to cover all the blitz
        commands and syntax, making sure that only the core
        instructions defined in the first macro lib.

Make a PPC and 68K version of the assembler and core macro library.

Then we have a future proof system.
Simply update the assembler and core macro library and all the blitz
commands still work......wow, how could a human think of such a
perfect system........

Someone tell me I'm being stupid......


Matt P.

A1200 040/25Mhz  PPC 603 240Mhz + 32megs fastram
soon to get BVision


@ENDNODE
