Subject: Re: Coloured text in GTLists

On 2 Oct 98, at 22:46, Eoghann Irving collapsed under the weight of:

> Hi :)
> 
> I'd like to be able to highlight certain items in a GTList.  I think I
> need to use a CallBackHook to do that, but I haven't the faintest idea h=
ow
> to go about it.
> 
> Anyone got an example?

 If you know C then look at aminet/dev/c/MultiList.lha which is an 
example for selecting Multiple items in a GTListView. It uses a 
callbackhook for this.

 A reminder for everyone: all hooks are exactly the same, so you can 
use the method for setting up hooks in the latest ASL filter 
screenmode crap (not the one on Aminet by me, it doesnt work). The 
only real difference will be whats in the hook high level function.


