@NODE "Mail_91" "Re: Colours"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Fri, 2 Oct 1998 20:28:29 +0100
From: "Nick Chapman" <scillo@geocities.com>
Subject: Re: Colours
Date: Sun, 27 Sep 1998 13:13:24 +0100

Hi there.

There are a number of things that could be wrong. If you are using a
Coplist, make sure that in the "type" part of the command, you add "6" to it
to make clear that you want 6 bitplanes. For basic usage, the "colours" part
of this command makes no difference.

Next, make sure that you have reserved enough colours in "InitPalette" and
also that the "Bitmap" has a great enough depth (6 in your case). If all of
the above fails, try resaving the image from DPaint/PPaint/whatever.

Nick

