@NODE "Mail_110" "Re: Devices and Lines"
Date: Wed, 14 Oct 1998 17:10:54 +0100
From: Adam Lounds <adaml@tcp.net.uk>
Subject: Re: Devices and Lines

On Wed, Oct 14, 1998 at 04:48:34PM +0100, Wright J.A said:
> > hello again,
> >                just 2 questions here,  
> > 
> > first, how can i get a list of the names of disks currently available, for
> > my app to display so the user can select one? 
> > 
> > second,  in a game i`ve coded a rotating 3d wireframe cube, it is only
> > drawn 1 colour at the moment using the Line command, however i`m drawing
> > it on a screen which is 2 bitplanes depth (4 cols). What i want to do is
> > make it so when a line intercepts another, that point of overlap is drawn
> > in a brighter colour...  i think i need to set up the palette so that col0
> > is Black and Cols1-3 are the colour of my cube from darker to lighter....
> > but i think i need to change the mode of the line draw so that it OR`s the
> > bitplanes?? is that right???  
> > and how the hell do you do it???????
> > 
> > thanks,
> > james
> > 

Hmm. Did you just resubmit the query or is it me?

If you do an OR, you'll just get a single colour for everything.
To get the desired overlap effect, you'll have to plot some
lines on one bitplane and the others on another. This will
involve either using 12 bitplanes (one for each line) or some
sort of depth sorting. See
http://www.geocities.com/SiliconValley/Lakes/5443/3dindex.html for 
a random altavista result from "depth sorting 3d" Looks like it's got
some source as well (in c++). Perhaps this will help.

later,
