@NODE "Mail_113" "Re: Double-Click"
          Paris Tue, 20 Oct 1998 23:02:57 +0200 (MET DST)
          Paris Tue, 20 Oct 1998 23:02:48 +0200 (MET DST)
From: Gigandet Jean-Marc <HURRICAN@wanadoo.fr>
Date: Tue, 20 Oct 1998 23:03:54 +0100
Subject: Re: Double-Click

You should use DoubleClick_, here is an example:

       Seconds.l     = 0 
       Micros.l      = 0  
       SSeconds.l    = 0
       SMicros.l     = 0 

; Somewhere in the program, when you get the first click
        Result = CurrentTime_(&SSeconds,&SMicros)

; Then when you get the second click 
        Result = CurrentTime_(&Seconds,&Micros)

; Then test the elapsed time :
        DBClic.b = DoubleClick_(SSeconds,SMicros,Seconds,Micros)
        If DBClic = true ...

Hope it's what you need !
Regards, ...



