Date: Mon, 26 Oct 1998 13:21:28 +0000
encoding: 7BIT
Subject: Enforcer hits


Hello all,

	After running my program with Enforcer, I noticed approx 16 
hits.  About an hour later I found the cause: Borders Off when using 
stringgadgets.  It`s not the Borders Off command that causes the 
hits just the definition of the stringgadgets afterwards (ie before 
opening a window with the gadgets).
	Does anyone have a clue on how to fix this or (even better) 
how to set up GTSTRINGS without a border?


	On another note, this isn`t really Blitz related, but how 
does the Save, Use, Cancel options of Prefs programs work?  
Obvoiulsy Cancel is just ignore, but what of Save and Use?
I think Save writes the prefs file to ENVARC: and makes a copy in 
RAM:ENV/   and Use just copies it to RAM:Env/.  Is this correct?

Thanks
Steven

(Amisheet v0.4 - on Aminet now) - Thanks to Rui for uploading it



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_117" "Re: Enforcer hits"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Mon, 26 Oct 1998 20:00:45 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Mon, 26 Oct 1998 20:54:40 +0000
Subject: Re: Enforcer hits

Hi,

>     On another note, this isn`t really Blitz related, but how 
> does the Save, Use, Cancel options of Prefs programs work?  
> Obvoiulsy Cancel is just ignore, but what of Save and Use?
> I think Save writes the prefs file to ENVARC: and makes a copy in 
> RAM:ENV/   and Use just copies it to RAM:Env/.  Is this correct?

I use these buttons in the preferences for Foundation. The Use button
will save the preferences to ram: which is where the main game will
first look. The Save button will save to the prefs/ directory. The Envarc:
idea is similar but I don't really like the concept of the Envarc:
directory.
Unless you use the handy startup hack HappyEnv you'd end up with a
huge amount of wasted memory with all the programs that dump prefs
files on there. I waste a few minutes each month clearing out the crap
from the Env-archive directory. It's not exactly elegant computing.

Cheers,

-- 
<- Paul Burkey <-> http://burkey.home.ml.org ->



@ENDNODE
