@NODE "Mail_136" "even or odd"
From: Roger Beausoleil <vision_fx@citenet.net>
Date: Sat, 31 Oct 1998 08:01:13 +0500
Subject: even or odd

Hi all Blitzers,

I would like to know if it is possible to read or identify ( with a command or
a tip ) a number in a variable as an even or odd number?

Exemple: a = 1   ; a is odd
          b = 2   ; b is even

Thanks in advance
Roger
  



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_137" "Re: even or odd"
From: Damir Arh <damir.arh@guest.arnes.si>
Date: Sat, 31 Oct 1998 15:27:44 +0100
Subject: Re: even or odd

Hi everyone!

On 31-Okt-98, Roger Beausoleil shared his opinion:

> Hi all Blitzers,
 
> I would like to know if it is possible to read or identify ( with a
command
> or a tip ) a number in a variable as an even or odd number?
 
> Exemple: a = 1   ; a is odd
>          b = 2   ; b is even

Try something like:

If a MOD 2=0
    NPrint "a is even"
Else
    NPrint "a is odd"
End If

It should do the job.

Kind regards from Slovenia
-- 
