@NODE "Mail_139" "Re: even or odd"
From: Sami =?iso-8859-1?Q?N=E4=E4t=E4nen?= <sami.naatanen@dlc.fi>
Date: Sun, 01 Nov 1998 00:12:05 +0200
Organization: Diverse
Subject: Re: even or odd
Encoding: quoted-printable

On 31-Oct-98, Roger Beausoleil wrote:
> Hi all Blitzers,

> I would like to know if it is possible to read or identify ( with a com=
mand
or
> a tip ) a number in a variable as an even or odd number?

> Exemple: a =3D 1   ; a is odd
>           b =3D 2   ; b is even

It depends where you need the info this is one usefull way:

even.w=3Dtrue; set up var, which tells you if the value is even or not

even.w=3D-(a.w&1); if A is odd number then this will return -1 =3D true e=
lse
                  it will be 0 =3D false

or if you just want the original variable to hold the odd or even thing y=
ou
can use this one

a.w=3Da.w&1; A will be NULL if even and ONE if ODD

if you need the number like odd -> var =3D 1 even -> var =3D 2 then use t=
his one

a.w=3D2-(a.w&1)

So there are much more usefull ways, but it depends the way you need and
use the info, so you have to get the best suited for your purpose.

