@NODE "Mail_141" "Re: Event commands..."
 (envelope-from D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    5 Oct 98 09:13:40 GMT+1
From: "David McMinn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University
Date: Mon, 5 Oct 1998 09:13:31 +0100
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Event commands...

On 4 Oct 98, at 15:57, Luca Carminati collapsed under the weight of:

> Hi there,
> 
> could someone tell me what the 'SetEventFilter' and 'EventiAddress'
> commands are for?

 Souns like SetEventFilter would get rid of any Events (in a mask or 
a list or something) before they reach your program. EventIAddress 
returns the IAddress field of an Event, handy for things like 
#IDCMP_GADGETHELP messages, where you can get a pointer to the gadget 
that caused it from the IAddress field.


