Subject: Re: Exec version!

On 2 Oct 98, at 19:51, Luca Carminati collapsed under the weight of:

> Hi Men,

     ^^^ ooh, not very PC (but who'd want to be an out of date 
computer :)
 
> is there a way to get the exec version without using the ExecVersion
> command (just to avoid an extra lib)?
> 
> Thanks...

Using amigalibs.res:

 *e.Library =3D peek.l(4)
exec_version.w =3D *e\LibNode\lib_Version

 Technically, *e should be ExecBase but I can't remember what the 
Library field ini ExecBase is called, and as its the first field, 
this works perfectly.


