@NODE "Mail_147" "Fast text loader"
  (SMTPD32-4.06) id A0D042D701BE; Wed, 14 Oct 1998 01:39:28 +00d0
From: "BootBlock/Carnage" <BootBlock@GeoCities.com>
Subject: Fast text loader
Date: Wed, 14 Oct 1998 03:38:25 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit

I've been reading about the fast text loader conversation that's been going
on, and I was meaning to post this little bit of code, bit kept forgetting.

Some of you may remember that I was doing an Amiga diskmag engine (The Word)
a long while back. It's been finished for quite a while and this text loader
code was taken from it. If you would like to see the mag, then download it
from: www.geocities.com/TimesSquare/Castle/4500 and follow the "The Word"
link and click on either "Alternative download site 1" or "Alternative
download site 2".

You can find this code below and other useful code snippets on my website in
my sig (There's not much there, but I'm adding to it!).


--- Here is the code.....

;
; Fast Text Loading thing V0.99
; by BootBlock/Carnage, 02/10/1998.
;
;  BootBlock@GeoCities.com
;  HTTP://fly.to/Parpsville
;
; This example loads a text files into a memory  block,
; counts the number of lines,  DIMs an array big enough
; to hold the  text,  puts  the  text  into  the array,
; free's the memory block and finally prints the entire
; array to the screen.
;
; Or basically: Loads a text file and displays it.
;
;
;
;
;
;

  PhileIn$ = "S:Startup-Sequence"        ;File to load in.



  ;--- Read in the file....
  ;
  If ReadFile(0,PhileIn$)<>0
    FLen.l  = Lof(0)
    Ptr.l   = AllocMem_(FLen,65536)
    ReadMem   0,Ptr,FLen
    CloseFile 0
  Else
    DisplayBeep_ 0
    PutStr_      Title$+Chr$(10)
    PutStr_      "  Error reading: "+PhileIn$+Chr$(10)+Chr$(10)
    End
  EndIf



;#########################################################COUNT LINES

    ;--- Count the lines in the file so we can
    ;    DIM the required array using the value...
    ;
    GetReg  a0,Ptr          ;put file's start addy in a0
    GetReg  d0,FLen         ;put file's length in d0

    MOVEQ.l #0,d1           ;clear d1
    MOVEQ.l #0,d4           ;clear d4 for our CR counter
_jump:
    MOVE.b  (a0),d3         ;move next char into d3 for checking
    CMP.b   $0a,d3          ;is it a carriage return?
    BNE    _jump2           ;nope, just to routine _jump2 ...
    ADDQ.l  #1,d4           ;it is! Add 1 to d4 (counter for # of CR's)
_jump2:
    ADDQ.l  #1,d1           ;add 1 to buffer's position
    ADDQ.l  #1,a0           ;move 1 char along buffer
    MOVE.l  d1,d2           ;compare file's length vs counter length
    CMP.l   d2,d0           ;end of buffer reached?
    BNE    _jump            ;Nope, go back to main loop...

    PutReg d4,lines.l       ;finally get the # of lines from d4
                            ;and put it in the lines variable.

    Dim    Lines$(lines)    ;Now make an array big enough to
                            ;hold all the lines
    Stop


  cpos.l  = Ptr


  ;--- Put all the lines into
  ;    an array....
  ;
  For lyne.l=0 To lines-1
    Lines$(lyne)=PeekTo$(cpos,10)
    cpos+Len(Lines$(lyne))+1
  Next lyne


  ;--- Free the allocated memory block...
  ;
  FreeMem_ Ptr,FLen


  ;--- Print out the array...
  ;
  For lyne.l=0 To lines-1
    NPrint Lines$(lyne)
  Next lyne

  MouseWait
  End




--
BootBlock/Carnage, from Grimsby, England. - ICQ#: 14864929
HTTP://fly.to/ParpsVille - Amiga/PC/PSX, Blitz2, Emulation, etc...
A1200T/020-28/iP166/2+4+32Mb/2.1+4.3Gb/56k/NEC4x4 (all in *1* case!)




@ENDNODE
