Subject: Re: Fill Newtype

On 10 Oct 98, at 17:54, Mathias PARNAUDEAU collapsed under the weight of:

> Hi all,
> 
> how is it possible to fill a declared NewType reading a block of memory
> (which size is equal to the amount of the newtype variables). I mean I
> want to move well ordered datas from memory to the newtype structure.

 If its already in memory then just use a pointer. Then access the 
fields you need and go on to the next one. If you need to get a copy 
of the memory, then use the OS CopyMem and associated functions.


