> first, how can i get a list of the names of disks currently available, for
> my app to display so the user can select one? 
> 
> second,  in a game i`ve coded a rotating 3d wireframe cube, it is only drawn
> 1 colour at the moment using the Line command, however i`m drawing it on a
> screen which is 2 bitplanes depth (4 cols). What i want to do is make it so
> when a line intercepts another, that point of overlap is drawn in a brighter
> colour...  i think i need to set up the palette so that col0 is Black and
> Cols1-3 are the colour of my cube from darker to lighter.... but i think i
> need to change the mode of the line draw so that it OR`s the bitplanes?? is
> that right???  
> and how the hell do you do it???????

Try using -1 as the color for the line.  This "inverts" it.  Maybe it will
give the effect you want, depending on how you set your palette. 


