@NODE "Mail_158" "format probs"
 ([62.136.2.142] helo=194.152.64.35 ident=stingent)
	by mail2.svr.freeserve.net with smtp (Exim 2.05iplimit-2 #4)
	id 0zYWWh-0000NL-00
	for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Wed, 28 Oct 1998 14:24:43 +0000
From: Bippy M <BippyM@stingent.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Wed, 28 Oct 1998 14:27:34 +0000
Subject: format probs

Hello Blitzers,

Oki I'm writing a small stats proggie that reads data from a memory bank!

okay firstly thee program has to read 3 bytes from the bank.. it needs to
find the following $00 02 00 or $00 78 00 00

I'm reading these into the variables  a, b, and c
and I then pass that to a string

i.e

PString$=str$(a)+str$(b)+str$(c)

then I check what is in PString$ with

If PString$="000200"
 SOME CODE
endif

now if I use the format command  FORMAT "00" str$ will return the correct
figures (00, 02, 00) etc...

but if I don't use the FORMAT command it returns 020 (which is no use)

Oki this is fine until later in the proggie...

I have the following routine

for J=0 to (number of times it found 000200)

    if name$(j)=nam$
        do aomething
next J

Oki the problem I get here is the array subscript error, even tho there are
2000 items in the array and the prog only writes to the first 4/5 locations!

I put a nprint J command in the string and It output:

0
0
1
?

I figure the ? is the problem, and it stems from the Format command.. what I
would like to know is. how do I put the FORMAT command back to its default?

Yours

Mark Green





@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_159" "Re: format probs"
 (envelope-from D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    28 Oct 98 14:44:03 GMT+1
From: "David McMinn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University
Date: Wed, 28 Oct 1998 14:43:51 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: format probs

On 28 Oct 98, at 14:27, Bippy M floundered in a pit of silicon hell:

> okay firstly thee program has to read 3 bytes from the bank.. it needs t=
o
> find the following $00 02 00 or $00 78 00 00

$00 78 00 00 is 4 bytes.
 
> I'm reading these into the variables  a, b, and c
> and I then pass that to a string
> 
> i.e
> 
> PString$=3Dstr$(a)+str$(b)+str$(c)
> 
> then I check what is in PString$ with
> 
> If PString$=3D"000200"
>  SOME CODE
> endif
>
> now if I use the format command  FORMAT "00" str$ will return the correc=
t
> figures (00, 02, 00) etc...

 What happens when you find $80 or above? if a=3D$80 (128 in decimal) 
then Format "00" will make str$ return "128". You need to use the 
Hex$ command to get hex digit srings from numbers, i.e.

PString$ =3D Hex$(a) + Hex$(b) + Hex$(c)
 
> Oki the problem I get here is the array subscript error, even tho there
> are 2000 items in the array and the prog only writes to the first 4/5
> locations!
> 
> I put a nprint J command in the string and It output:
> 
> 0
> 0
