 Remember that your Nprint will have its output altered by Format, so 
that might not be causing the problem with the array. It may only 
look like it.
 From your code, you use J as the loopvariable, but access the array 
with j - both are quite different, although I don't think this would 
cause an array subscript out of range error (that's the one you 
mean?), as j would be 0 all the time.

 Unless you've used j somewhere else and ended up with it equal to 
<*big*>.


