> with j - both are quite different, although I don't think this would 
> cause an array subscript out of range error (that's the one you 
> mean?), as j would be 0 all the time.

I use j only, I use lowercase letters for ALL my for..Next loops...
 
> Unless you've used j somewhere else and ended up with it equal to 
> <*big*>.

Nope! erm, here is the source below...

Basically the program I'm writing reads info from the .pkt files outputted
by message programs (Spot etc...) The beginning of each message starts with
$00 02 00 so I've been checking from there! Have a look and tell me what you
think...
Also ignore the messy code, as I'm just testing atm...




Dim name$(2000)
Dim name2$(2000)
Dim value(2000)

For i.l=0 To 2000
  name2$(i)=" "
Next i

LoadBank 0,"bbs:12cd.pkt"
q.l=Bank(0)
q.l+66
ln.l=Exists("bbs:12cd.pkt")


pos.l=0                    ; Position of Writers Name
.pek

; Peek to find the Writers Name
v=0
NPrint "Please Wait.. Searching"
For i.l=0 To ln

;Format "00"

    a.b=NPeekB(q+i)
    b.b=NPeekB(q+i+1)
    c$=Peeks$(q+i+4,4)



If a=0 AND b=78
Print a
Print b
Print c

ka$=Str$(a)+Str$(b)+Str$(c)
NPrint" ":Print ka$
EndIf


If ka$="020"
;  NPrint ka$
  pos.l=q+i+35
  name$(v)=PeekTo$(pos,$00)
;  NPrint name$(v)
  v+1
EndIf

Next i

 NPrint "Total Message Writers Are:"+Str$(v)
 NPrint " "

For p=0 To v
  NPrint name$(p)
Next p

Format "#"

For i=0 To v
  nam$=name$(i)


  For j.b=0 To v

    If nam$=name2$(j)
      value(j)+1
      d=2000-j
      j=v+d
    EndIf

 NPrint j

    If name2$(j)=" "
      name2$(j)=nam$
      value(j)+1
      navail+1
      oki=1
      d=v-j
      j=j+d
    EndIf

  Next j
Next i

Stop

For i=1 To navail-1
  NPrint name2$(i) + " Has Written "+Str$(value(i))+" Messages"
Next

Repeat
Until Joyb(0)=3


Thanks

Mark Green



@ENDNODE
