@NODE "Mail_164" "format probs"
From: hotcakes@abacus.net.au
Date: 29 Oct 1998 22:44:40 EDT
Subject: format probs

BI>I figure the ? is the problem, and it stems from the Format command.. what I
BI>would like to know is. how do I put the FORMAT command back to its default?

Try

Format ""

I think that's correct?

Anyway, that all sounds a little dodgy to me.  If you're converting hex
numbers into a string the best way to do it is :

PString$=Hex$(a)+Hex$(b)+Hex$(c)

I've noticed Hex$ doesn't put the $'s in front of the numbers, which is
actually quite handy =]

