In fact the SetInt command is bugged and only works well with the 
Vertical Blank Interrupt. So any other type aren't going to work unless you 
program this! But as i have already mentioned. All these stuff is 
already programmed in the Virtual Blitter Library code. 

I'm using some o.s. functions that will let it work in multitasking too. 
still there are some work to do for the cookie-cut blitting, but you can 
use it to do any block-type blits you need. Please check the code and if 
you have troubles understanding it, e-mail me again.

Also if you can help with the cookie-cut operations it would be a 
pretty good thing :)

Thanks for reading.

Carlos Villarroel


