@NODE "Mail_175" "Re: Get File Size"
From: Sami =?iso-8859-1?Q?N=E4=E4t=E4nen?= <sami.naatanen@dlc.fi>
Date: Fri, 09 Oct 1998 23:22:44 +0200
Organization: Diverse
Subject: Re: Get File Size
Encoding: quoted-printable

On 10-Oct-98, Mathias PARNAUDEAU wrote:
> Hey Blitzers !

> Just an easy question (except for me) : What is the way to konw the siz=
e of
a
> file with the system (OS) functions (like Open_, Close_, ...). I know t=
he
> command
> is Lof(x) in Blitz ;-)

I don't remember correctly the syntax, but firstly open the file with
fh=3Dopen_(filename,mode)
and then
pos=3Dseek_(fh,0,mode)
and then the second seek (you can seek the end
again) and it will return the length of the file.

so:

fh.l=3Dopen_("ram:myfile",oldfile)
pos.l=3D0
if fh>0
  pos.l=3Dseek_(fh,-1,0)
  pos.l=3Dseek_(fh,-1,0)
endif

if pos>0 then nprint "File length is "+str$(pos)+"."

end
         _____________________________________________________
