Hi,

>  Has anyone Written or Got any code that give you access to GFX Card's that i
> can look at and Modify if Possible to Work on the PPC GFX Card . 

the PPC gfx card works the same as any other gfx card. They are all
supported by CGFX and/or Picasso96 so all you have to do is use
graphics.library functions and/or stick system friendly Blitz commands
like Windows, Screens and all Window rendering functions.

I wrote Foundation before PPC gfx cards were available and also before
the Ateo gfx cards. When they became available they were given
support for P96 or CyberGFX so the game was instantly compatable.

Cheers,

-- 
Paul Burkey <--> http://burkey.home.ml.org <-->



