Hi,

> Well I was talking to Daniel Allsop about this and he suggested
> WriteChunkyPixels_, which I've looked at and it seems to do what I
> want - a source horizontal modulo. However, it doesn't tokenise in the
> blitz I've got. Is this the same for everyone else also I wonder? I
> could I suppose open gfx lib. It's probably o/s 3.1? I'll probably
> have to put in the write pixel line8 fallback mode.

Yes, WriteChunkyPixels() is part of OS3.1 but Blitz only has
functions up to OS3.0. All you need it to convert the .fd file
for OS3.1 graphics.library and you'd have the new function.
That wouldn't be so good if you wanted to support the remaining
users with OS3.0 or (shock horror!) an even older OS!

Cheers,

-- 
Paul Burkey <--> http://burkey.home.ml.org <-->



