@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_194" "Re: GT = Good Try | Get Tipsy ??"
 (envelope-from D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    7 Oct 98 09:41:54 GMT+1
From: "David McMinn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University
Date: Wed, 7 Oct 1998 09:41:43 +0100
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: GT = Good Try | Get Tipsy ??

On 7 Oct 98, at 0:39, Andrew Drays collapsed under the weight of:

> this code.. but the constants don't do be a bit of good if I don't
> understand them and what they're for.. or what they do?! or how they're

Autodocs......

> ;  GTTags #GT_Underscore,"_",#STRINGA_ExitHelp,1

#GT_Underscore sets the character which is to be interpreted as 
causing your gadget labels to have an underscore. i.e. with the 
above, if your gadget label was _Source then it would be displayed as 
Source
=3D

#STRINGA_ExitHelp (true / false) is a tag which causes the string 
gadget to stop being edited when the Help key is pressed and cause 
IDCMP events for RawKey (for the help key) and probably a GadgetUp 
for the string gadget.

> ;  GTTags #GT_Underscore,"_",#GA_TabCycle,1,#STRINGA_ExitHelp,1

#GA_TabCycle (true / false) means that when you press Tab or Shift-
Tab, the next or previous string gadget (that has TabCycle set) will 
become active.

> ;  GTTags #GTTX_Border,1
#GTTX_Border (0, 1 or 2) is the border style of a text (read only) gadget.

> ;  GTTags #GTLV_ScrollWidth,16,#LAYOUTA_Spacing,1
#GTLV_ScrollWidth is the width of scroll bars and arrows.

#LAYOUTA_Spacing is the extra space to put between items in the 
listview.


|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
