@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_196" "Re: GTGZZPosition"
From: Luca Carminati <toffi@spm.it>
Date: Sat, 31 Oct 1998 11:45:36 -0500
Subject: Re: GTGZZPosition
Encoding: quoted-printable

On 27-Ott-98, Martin Au=DFem wrote:

>Hi,

>can anyone tell me
>what`s the function of the GTGZZPosition-Command?

Hi Martin,

I don't know if someone else answered your question, but...

When you put a GTGadget on a non-GIMME00 window, its co-ordinates start f=
rom
the inner top-left corner. But if the window is a GIMME00 one, the top an=
d
left border sizes are added to the gadget's co-ordinates. The 'GTGZZPosit=
ion
On' command simply avoid this behaviour.

I hope this is clear enough.

C ya...




-- =

Best regards,

Luca.

