From: "BootBlock/Carnage" <BootBlock@GeoCities.com>
	"blitz" <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Subject: Re: gtlistview
Date: Wed, 14 Oct 1998 09:38:55 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit

Andrew wrote:


>ok.. I've been getting a lot of stuff done.. and having fun doing it..
>
>my latest dilemma.. .. I'm got stuff going tinto a listview.. and it's
>constantly haivng input come in.. from IRC.. how do I have my listview
stick
>with scolling what's on the bottom instead of the TOP? so as input comes
in..
>it keeps going down.. sntead of having to keep moving the scroll bar?!?


Use the GTHighlight (or it might be GTSetHighlight) command with the Index
command directly after you modify the listview, like so:

  Dim List Bum.Hole(100)

  GTHighlight List#,ID,Index(BumHole())


I think that's the syntax for the GTHighlist command...

