@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_220" "Re: GTScroller"
          Paris Sun, 4 Oct 1998 22:04:58 +0200 (MET DST)
          Paris Sun, 4 Oct 1998 22:04:50 +0200 (MET DST)
From: Gigandet Jean-Marc <HURRICAN@wanadoo.fr>
Date: Sun, 04 Oct 1998 01:03:42 +0100
Subject: Re: GTScroller
Encoding: quoted-printable

Hi !
you can use things like this :

1) Define your gadget
  GTScroller  GTListNumber,#Gen_Ascen,XPosition,YPosition,Width,Height,As=
sociatedText$,#_Immediate+#_Vertical,1,1
  *PGen_Ascen.Gadget  =3D GTGadPtr(GTListNumber,#Gen_Ascen)
1b) For a better look (since 2.0) add this lines :
  *PropI.PropInfo          =3D *PGen_Ascen\SpecialInfo
  *PropI\Flags               =3D *PropI\Flags | #PROPNEWLOOK

2) When you want to change, refresh, your scroller :
    GTSetAttrs GTListNumber,#Gen_Ascen,#GTSC_Total,TotalNumber,#GTSC_Top,=
Position,#GTSC_Visible,WidthOfKnob
    Redraw GTListNumber,#Gen_Ascen

For example, if your scroller indicates the position 20 in a list of 100 =
                TotalNumber =3D 100
                Position =3D 20
                WidthOfKnob =3D Number of Items visible at a time
                         (for a value of 50 you'll have a knob half the s=
ize of the scroller).
Regards, ...=



