@NODE "Mail_223" "Re: GTstring activate"
          Thu, 29 Oct 1998 12:38:17 +0000
          29 Oct 98 12:38:16 +0000
From: "S.J.CROY" <ap6013@qmw.ac.uk>
Organization: University of London (QMW)
Date: Thu, 29 Oct 1998 12:38:07 +0000
encoding: 7BIT
Subject: Re: GTstring activate


Recently, Andrew Drays had this to say:

> I know activatesting will work for standard stings.. but I'm looking 
for a
> similar command or gttag for GTstring.. 
> 
> any help??

I always use this:
 ActivateGadget_ GTGadPtr(1,0),Peek.l(Addr Window(1)),0

Make sure the window is active first before calling this though (Use 
the Activate command)

I don`t know if Curt`s answer would work - I haven`t tried, but Ive 
found parts of the gadget library cause massive Enforcer hits in 
your executable, so I`d try leaving them alone.


Hope this helps
Steven



