I think AGA is becoming more of just a normal display device, as would
be a graphics card, rather than the additional features such as
blitter, sprites, and copperlist effects. They used to be really cool
when the standards were at that level that you dual playfields were
acceptable and most things whizzed along at 50Hz, but as you say these
days people have realised you can only do this up to a limit before
the hardware starts to be less efficient than CPU. I'm glad you're
redoing foundation in chunky and if you want some help with that c2p
then give me a yell. It can handle those `windows' you talked about
now, although horizontal width has to be to the nearest 32 pixels.


