From: Thomas Newsom <thomas.newsom@allhours.karoo.co.uk>
Date: Fri, 02 Oct 1998 13:42:48 +0100
Organization: The Open All Hours BBS @ +44-(0)1482-345494 & +44-(0)1482-447576 24 hours
Subject: Help?

Hi,

Is it possible to include an executable in a compiled Blitz program that one
can call and run?

What I'm refering to is. If say I have a normal Amiga executable I want to be
able to get Blizt to compile my program with this executable compiled within,
then within the program this included program would be called.

I hope that makes sense :)
 
Cheers
