 via smail with P:esmtp/R:smart_host/T:smtp
	(sender: <Andreas.Falkenhahn@gmx.de>) 
	id <m0zPBdg-001nulC@insider.regio.net>
	for <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>; Fri, 2 Oct 1998 21:17:20 +0100 (MET)
	(Smail-3.2.0.101 1997-Dec-17 #1 built DST-Jul-17)
From: Andreas Falkenhahn <Andreas.Falkenhahn@gmx.de>
Date: Fri, 02 Oct 1998 22:13:31 +0100
Organization: Airsoft Softwair
Subject: Re: Help?

Hi Thomas
Am 02-Okt-98 schrieb Thomas Newsom:

> Hi,
> 
> Is it possible to include an executable in a compiled Blitz program that one
> can call and run?
yes that`s possible
> 
> What I'm refering to is. If say I have a normal Amiga executable I want to
be
> able to get Blizt to compile my program with this executable compiled
within,
> then within the program this included program would be called.
You should not do that because it would be very dirty kind of programming.
But if you want to do so: I would do it like that...

filesize.l=<<<enter here the filesize>>>
success.l=BSave("Ram:Myprog", ?exe, filesize)

Execute_ "Ram:Myprog",0,0
Delete_ "Ram:myprog"

End

.includes
exe: Include "C:MyProg"

That should work.



> 
> I hope that makes sense :)
> 
> Cheers
Regards
-- 
