@NODE "Mail_256" "Re: How can i test if a window was opened?"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Sat, 10 Oct 1998 02:43:40 +0000
From: "Dave" <dave@nbsamiga.demon.co.uk>
Subject: Re: How can i test if a window was opened?
Date: Sun, 4 Jan 1998 09:36:37 -0000
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit


On 05-Ott-98, Christian Uceda wrote:

>Hello everybody

>same as the subject: how can i know if a window was opened or not?
>i have no idea, i'm a beginner in OS and GUI


 If you mean how to test if a window you asked for actually opened, this
should do

If peek.l(addr window(1))<>0 then win1.b=true else win1.b=false

 Which sets a variable (win1) to true, if window 1 was actually opened,
otherwise it sets it to false. For other windows simply replace the 1`s with
the window number you`d like to test. Hope that helps...

Dave




@ENDNODE
