@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_260" "Re: How to handle c: calls ?"
X-Ncc-Regid: de.netcologne
From: "M. Misic" <m.misic@netcologne.de>
Date: Sat, 03 Oct 1998 17:33:33 +0200
Organization: Checkpoint BBS
Subject: Re: How to handle c: calls ?

Hallo Andreas,\n

>> 1. How i get lha's output ?
> For example:
> 
> *suc.l=Execute_("C:LHA >CON:0/0/640/256/LHA Output/AUTO/CLOSE/WAIT x
> sys:myarchive.lha RAM:"+Chr$(0),0,0
> 
> This opens a window 640x256 at x,y=0 and displays lha`s output in it! 

An output-window appears, but lha works bad in case of using ">CON:".

Without redirecting to CON: it works fine, but with it the given path- and
filenames would't reconised and lha's output (in encode-mode) will allways
named "a.lha" and always stored in PROGDIR:. :(

-- 
Mastervoice    Sysop der Checkpoint BBS
               Node 0   02235 - 42474 (V.34)
               Node 1   02235 - 922866(ISDN X.75)

