@NODE "Mail_265" "IncBin"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Wed, 28 Oct 1998 23:16:45 +0000
From: Stuart Walker <stuart@digital-images.demon.co.uk>
Date: Wed, 28 Oct 1998 20:50:21 +0000
Subject: IncBin 

Hello,

Does anyone know how you use the IncBin command with Blitz 2? Please give
some example code.

Best Regards

Stuart Walker

Digital Images

e-mail:stuart@digital-images.demon.co.uk
Website:http://www.digital-images.demon.co.uk



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_266" "Re: IncBin"
          Thu, 29 Oct 1998 12:43:47 +0000
          29 Oct 98 12:43:46 +0000
From: "S.J.CROY" <ap6013@qmw.ac.uk>
Organization: University of London (QMW)
Date: Thu, 29 Oct 1998 12:43:12 +0000
encoding: 7BIT
Subject: Re: IncBin 


Stuart Walker can be quoted as saying


> Hello,
> 
> Does anyone know how you use the IncBin command with Blitz 2? Please give
> some example code.
 
Ok, this is dead easy. Here`s an example


.main
decodeshapes 0,?shapedata
....program code

shapedata
incbin "wb3.0:graphics/shapes"
Even

Notice that shapedata doesn`t have a full stop before it. It can have 
one, but then it shows up on Ted`s window as a subroutine.
Then even command at the end just fixes the counter`s and stuff so 
you can have program code AFTER the subroutine shapedata.

Hope this helps
Steven



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_267" "Re: IncBin"
 id 0zYrl4-00077v-00; Thu, 29 Oct 1998 13:04:59 +0000
Date: Thu, 29 Oct 1998 05:03:17 -0800 (PST)
From: Thomas Cobb <thomcobb@yahoo.com>
Subject: Re: IncBin 






---Stuart Walker wrote:

> Does anyone know how you use the IncBin command with Blitz 2? Please
give
> some example code.

try this:

DecodeSound 0,?mysound	;decode sound included
			;at label mysound into object 1
Sound 0,15		;and play it

End

.mysound
IncBin "TheSound"

=====================================
BUT there are a few pitfalls...

DecodeShapes takes a shapes file, not an ilbm file

IncBin is interpreted during compile time so you can't use variables
in the name
e.g.

Path$ = "Blitz2:Programs/"
IncBin Path$+"theshapes"

is interpreted by the compiler as 

Include "Path$+"theshapes""

giving an error


	Thom
