@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_268" "IncBin"
From: hotcakes@abacus.net.au
Date: 29 Oct 1998 22:58:18 EDT
Subject: IncBin

ST>Does anyone know how you use the IncBin command with Blitz 2? Please give
ST>some example code.

Hey, here's something that's doubtless allready been answered, but look,
I can actually do this =] So here goes :)

Now it depends what you want to have Incced, as to how to decode it.
There are Decodexxxx commands for most major Blitz objects...

.new:
  DecodeShapes x,y,?_shapes
End    ; Fancy stuff, I know =]

._shapes:
  IncBin "blitz2:shapes/myshapesthatarereallycoolandilikeemheaps.shp"
Even

The ? is extremely useful in Blitz.  By prepending it to a labelname, it
will return the address in memory that the labelname is located.  I use
this mainly for storing any $VER: strings up the TOP of my program,
instead of the bottom ;]

