Subject: Re: key input in BLITZ

On 14 Oct 98, at 14:41, stocksjames collapsed under the weight of:

> I want to read keys in an arcade loop, but from what I remember, using
> inkey (? I think) ,the program just waited (froze) for a key input? How
> can I read a key just like a joystick button?

 RawKey(#keynumber) tells you whether the specified key is currently 
being pressed or not. There's a big list of the keynumbers at the 
back of the manual.

 P.S. Sorry about my reply to your MOD problems I thought you meant 
music MODs.


