On 13-Oct-98, stocksjames wrote:
> Gigandet Jean-Marc wrote:
> > =

> > What are you using exactly ?
> > Standard Blitz 2.1 : the original big Deflibs works fine.
> > RED SupportSuite : works also fine.
> > Did you rebuild your deflibs ?
> > The best way to do this is the LibMan program, that you can find on B=
um9.

> Er... the first one... big deflibs, eh? It's just that command. Is ther=
e
> another way to find the remainder?

function.w modulo{m1.l,m2.w}  ; remainder.w=3Dmodulo{dividend.l,divider}
  divs d1,d0
;  clr.w d0   ; this one can be used to make the remainder LONG
;              Just change the function type to .l and uncomment the clr
  swap d0
  asmexit
end function


This should work! Don't bet all my money on that though. ;)

