utilize the AGA chipset to any degree. The RTG support for example
was written in just over a week. =


>> optimized Asm rendering. That way the majority of Foundations users
>> (gfx card/040+ users) would be playing a game that is 2-3 times as fas=
t
>> and smooth and the rest would have something to look forward to
>> when they upgraded. =


> One moment, i never have seen your game in action, but i'm refuse to
> think that it's slower than the old settlers that ran in a bare A500??

I prefer not to get into comparisons with the speed and complexity
between Settlers and Foundation. The game engine is MANY times
more complex and so the speed even on an 030/50 is not very
impressive.

> Your game must be pretty complex.  Anyway the sort of programming you
> are doing for this can be speed up with a blitter c2p library (at least=
 for
> a 320x200 screen).

I doubt a Blitter based c2p could make the game any faster, especially
if I had to rener the screen in chip ram. It would probably be many
times slower.

> That is true, as you have used a chunky buffer, but the C2P conversion
> MUST be done by blitter since your game need all the CPU it can get.

Do you agree with Paul Wests claim that a blitter based c2p must
