@NODE "Mail_316" "MUList problems... solved! :)"
From: eNTiTy <entity@zeelandnet.nl>
Date: Fri, 02 Oct 1998 02:40:40 +0100
Subject: MUList problems... solved! :)

Hi,

Just thought i'd tell you that I solved the flicker-when-items-removed problem
(sort of)!

I was looking at AmIRC 2.1, which also have limited number of lines in
scrollback buffer, so I put the listview way back to top and started
generating lines until the buffer filled... I found that AmIRC cheats here:
If (max) plus (threshold) lines are reached, it removes (threshold) lines from
the top in one go, so after that you're left with (max) lines in the display.
Needless to say I assimilated this mechanism ;^) I guess Oliver had the same
problem, and came up with this nifty solution. Now it only flickers once every
this many lines, which is acceptable.

Bye!



@ENDNODE
