Subject: Re: New Amiga's classic emulation

On 26-Oct-98, Paul wrote:
>Blitzwing,

>(Did you mean to call yourself that?)

>> One other side thought, since the new machines have a unified
>> memory architecture, how much faster a C2P routines going to be ?

>What does that mean exactly? One type of memory only? Hmm. 

  Yes, all video and sound uses the main Ram- so you have as much video
ram as you have memory- nice! All memory accesses go through a special
chip that coordinates everything- check out the Pre\Box description on
P5's site for more details- they have some cool ideas for displaying
stuff, like showing bits of memory anywhere on a screen- no display
bitmaps anymore!

