@NODE "Mail_325" "Re: New Amiga's classic emulation"
From: Stephen Fellner <sfell@xtra.co.nz>
Date: Mon, 26 Oct 1998 18:30:40 +1200
Subject: Re: New Amiga's classic emulation

On 25-okt-98, Blitzwing wrote:
>Heya Blitzers, question......

>I've read the new O.S 4 amiga's have "classic" emulation is roughly 68040/33
>or so I've read. Does anyone know about it's compatability, more
specifically,
>can we use Blitz on it ? I'm buying one of these beast very shortly, but I
>won't if I can't use Blitz on it. Anyone know ?

It's claimed to be released some time next year, but there isn't much
technical data about it...  and it looks very much like it'll be just a PC
running some new AmigaOS, which doesn't exist yet... :) Don't expect miracles
from it. It won't have any fancy new chipsets, most likely a standard VGA IC
for graphics, and who knows maybe a PC soundcard for audio...

>One other side thought, since the new machines have a unified memory
>architecture, how much faster a C2P routines going to be ?

You won't need a c2p routine as the machine will have plenty of chunky modes
available, like any other VGA-based machine :) I'd be surprised if you could
emulate even some old A500 platform game, scrolling smoothly at 50 fps. And
the c2p routines' speed will depend on the emulation, and I'd say that it'll
be software emulation, using UAE. UAE isn't that bad on a 450 Mhz Pentium-II

--
Stephen



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_326" "Re: New Amiga's classic emulation"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Mon, 26 Oct 1998 13:02:30 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Mon, 26 Oct 1998 13:41:01 +0000
Subject: Re: New Amiga's classic emulation

Hi,

>>  One other side thought, since the new machines have a unified memory
>>  architecture, how much faster a C2P routines going to be ?

> Erm the new machines will have UMA, yes. The Emulator will not. The new
> machines will use some crap PC graphics board so C2P is not aplicable.

If you go back to the original topic of Classic emulation you would
realise that C2P would still be aplicable since the emulation would
be emulating "classic" AGA planar modes. However, the classic
emulation could also be fitted with good P96 and/or CyberGraphX
emulation in which case C2P wouldn't be necessary. It depends
how clever the classic emulation is.

At the end of the day Blitz will always be running in "classic" mode
so the you simply have to think about current technology and pray
that future technology can run it a hell of a lot faster and smoother! :)

Cheers,

-- 
