@NODE "Mail_336" "NewCommandSet 1.40 is finished"
From: =?iso-8859-1?Q?Fr=E9d=E9ric?= Laboureur <alphasnd@hol.fr>
Date: Wed, 14 Oct 1998 20:54:57 +0100
Organization: Fantaisie Software
Subject: NewCommandSet 1.40 is finished
Encoding: quoted-printable


    Hello Blitzers,

    The NCS (NewCommandSet) V1.40 is finished.

    Changes:

        + GadTools library finally corrected and finished (and optimized =
        + XPK Library include
        + New palette library which allow you to fade out a 640*480*256 A=
GA
        screen (MultiScan) PERFECTLY (At the VBlank). The Fadeout routine=

        is very optimized. This palette lib support AGA in standard BUT
        it requiers the Rom 3.0 at least. Everyone has rom3.0+ now :-).
        + New WbStartup lib to save 300 bytes against the old one.
        + Lot of bug fix, optim... More examples.

    If you're interrested, mail me...

        AMIGA - Back for the future - AMIGA

    =

            Bye,

                        Fred.

PS: For all who doensn't know, NCS is a command set replacement for old =

blitz libs to create really small'n'fast executables. It's easy to use
and to install.
