From: Carlos Villarroel Cortes <carlosv@redes.unam.mx>
Subject: Off topic??


Dr. Jonathan B. Postel, director of the Computer Networks division at
the Information Sciences Institute (ISI) of the University of Southern
California, and director of the Internet Assigned Numbers Authority,
passed away Friday, October 16th, in Los Angeles. 

He is (was) responsible and author of the most important TCP/IP 
protocols: IP, TCP, UDP, etc.

Please take a look at www.iana.org if you are interested.


