@NODE "Mail_346" "Re: Other Mailing Lists"
From: Donovan Reeve <bubby.lnk@ispi.net>
Date: Tue, 13 Oct 1998 21:00:55 +0500
Subject: Re: Other Mailing Lists

On 12-Oct-98, Garry Newman flashed:

> Can anyone recomend some other mailing lists, amiga or
> non amiga I dont give a duck!

>   This list is pretty slow, I always imagined it to be buzzing!

>  C-YA!


  Well, it's buzzing enough for me.  People know that they can come here
and get answers from knowledgable and helpful other users.  If there are
times when not much is being said it is because everybody is busy
working and not in great need of help at the moment.  Sometimes the list
is swamped, when someone statrs a discussion which many are interested
in or have information or opinions on.  Even though we have fun here and
joke around some, the main purpose of this list is to help each other
and spread information about Blitz Basic, not to entertain the bored.
If it is constant and varied entertainment you seek then yes, you probably
had better go elswhere because that isn't the purpose of this list.

  This list exists to help and educate, not to buzz.


Donovan Reeve (bubby.lnk@ispi.net)




@ENDNODE
