Hi everyone,

I'm posting this on behalf of James Boyd, who currently has no internet
connection. I looked at the source, but I can't seem to get the commands to
even tokenize (see other posting).

Can anyone help wit this?

*** Forwarded message, originally written by James Boyd on 06-Oct-98 ***
Hi Curt,

I`ve got a problem,and hoping you can help me!

I spent 4 hours last night trying to use powerpacker.library
to unpack a ppacked text file,and I`ve almost got it working,
but I`m getting a file written out which is a total mess.

Could you have a look,and if that fails,try the Blitz list for me?
Please? ;)

Basically,it uses a function which is supposed to do all the dirty 
work,and allocates the necessary memory to unpack the file.The problem 
is that it`s putting the length of the alloc`d memory into the address 
buffer,so that for ,eg,a 70k output file,it allocates 70k at the address 
70,000! Which is a bummer,and causes enforcer hits,as well as just 
putting the contents of that memory location into my file...

I`ve annotated the source - it needs powerpacker.fd FDConv`d (in 
aminet/utils/libs/pp16.lha)...


See ya,

James

**** END OF FOWARDED MESSAGE


                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


