    PPC will be supported if the langage evoluate right. But if the Amiga=
OS
don't move quickly in pure PPC code, I don't know the advantage to have a=
 PPC
exec for OS proggy. The functions must be adressed in 68000 code (OS func=
tions
takes there argument in 68000 registers...) so any call to an OS function=
 will
contain a code which switch between the 2 cpu. The PPC will be faster, ri=
ght,
but also much more bigger.

    But using fast and optimized PPC library for intensive functions (MAT=
HS,
Blitting stuffs, c2p, 2d or 3d drawing...) is really cool...

    Regards,

                        Fred.

