@NODE "Mail_372" "Re: PPC Blitz"
 (envelope-from 9430000@student.eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    12 Oct 98 12:57:46 0
From: "Evan Tuer" <9430000@student.eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Mon, 12 Oct 1998 12:57:35 GMT0BST
encoding: 7BIT
Subject: Re: PPC Blitz

> > 
> > Great - do it!   Oh, and leave the source "open" like Linux, and we 
> > might end up ridding the world of 'C' :-)
> 
>     And Microsoft will recompile it for Windows. No for me :-). Why WindowsNT
> is better each version ? Because it's being transformed in Linux even more
> each time...

Windows NT has 8 times as many lines of code as Linux, and will 
never be as good.  With a proper, legally correct PD statement (or 
whatever) Microsoft could recompile it all they want, but they 
certainly couldn't sell or include it in Windows.  

Anyway why should they want to, or any other big company?   
Microsoft push what they have, not what's best - make the product 
freeware, otherwise they could buy whoever owns the copyright and 
crush the project.   Why do you think OS2 died out?  

