@NODE "Mail_374" "Re: problem with EOF registering at all??"
From: Rick Hodger <rick.thehub@bigfoot.com>
Date: Mon, 05 Oct 1998 10:25:03 +0000
Organization: Corrupted Software
Subject: Re: problem with EOF registering at all??

I watched as Rudolf Sanchez hammered "problem with EOF registering at
all??" out on their keyboard...


RS> I am still working on article editor for a disk mag.  I noticed on
my system
RS> that EOF does not seem to register on my setup.  Has anyone else
notice this
RS> problem on their setup?  The read file continues without exiting
at EOF.  I
RS> was forced to use statement:  While loc(0)<>lof(0)

I get the same thing, but I never did find out why.  I always use
Repeat -> Until loops with "Until Lof(1)=Loc(1)" at the end.

RS> I noticed that location in file eventually equals length of file,
as you
RS> read in the file.  By the way, what is wrong with the following
routine?  I
RS> am almost certain something is awfully wrong with it but what??

<SNIP>

You're using a "WPrintScroll" before you actually print anything to
the window.  Your print or nprint command should be in front of the
WPrintScroll command.

-- 
