@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_375" "Re: problem with EOF registering at all??"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Mon, 5 Oct 1998 15:14:15 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Mon, 05 Oct 1998 11:40:41 +0000
Subject: Re: problem with EOF registering at all??

Hi,

> I am still working on article editor for a disk mag.  I noticed on my system
> that EOF does not seem to register on my setup.  Has anyone else notice this
> problem on their setup?  The read file continues without exiting at EOF.  I
> was forced to use statement:  While loc(0)<>lof(0)

I usually use:

While Eof(0)=False
   ; read file....   
Wend

That works fine. but also "While NOT Eof(0)" works fine too!

> I noticed that location in file eventually equals length of file, as you
> read in the file.  By the way, what is wrong with the following routine?  I
> am almost certain something is awfully wrong with it but what??

There was nothing obvious wrong with the source you sent. It seems
to run as expected. The only problem as the file requester which looks
a bit nasty compared to an ASL requester (proportional fonts etc..).

>  If ReadFile(0,f$)
>    FileInput 0
>    While NOT Eof(0)
>    i$=Edit$(77)
>    WPrintScroll:NPrint i$
>    Wend
>  <...snipped...>
>  EndIf

The above part in particular was working fine. You did forget to close
the file afterwards which could cause problems IF you're doing any
other file access work. So, it's usually best to close files *inside* the
"If ReadFile...EndIf" part since thats the only place th file could be
opened.

Cheers,

-- 
Paul Burkey <--> http://burkey.home.ml.org <-->



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_376" "Re: problem with EOF registering at all??"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Mon, 05 Oct 1998 06:43:10 -0500
Subject: Re: problem with EOF registering at all??

Warning: This is a message in MIME format. Your mail reader does not
support MIME. Some parts of this message will be readable as plain text.
To see the rest, you will need to upgrade your mail reader.


--BOUNDARY.1748147168.1

Hi Rudy,

On 04-Oct-98, Rudolf Sanchez wrote:
> Hi Blitz Pals:
> 
> I am still working on article editor for a disk mag.  I noticed on my system
> that EOF does not seem to register on my setup.  Has anyone else notice this
> problem on their setup?  The read file continues without exiting at EOF.  I
> was forced to use statement:  While loc(0)<>lof(0)

Your code seemed to work OK here.  There were a few mistakes - I have attached
a corrected version with some comments.  But the EOF did work on my system,
even with the original code.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1748147168.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="readtext.asc"
Encoding: quoted-printable

WBStartup:NoCli
WBenchToFront_

WbToScreen 0:   ;ShowScreen 0  Don't need - you already put WB in front

;Window 0,0,0,640,200,$1|$2|$4|$8,"RW",2,1

;Adding Gimme0 flag ($400) to window for using WPrintScroll command
;this prevents text from writing on the borders
Window 0,0,0,640,200,$1|$2|$4|$8|$400,"RW",2,1

MaxLen path$=3D250
;MaxLen fi$=3D64
MaxLen fi$=3D192           ;these both must always be at least 192

;f$=3DFileRequest$("Select a text File",path$,fi$)


;I substituted ASLfilerequest$ instead - this will use blitz requester fo=
r WB 1.xx,
;but uses much better ASL requester For WB 2.xx AND 3.xx

f$=3DASLFileRequest$("Select a text File",path$,fi$)

; pathnames$
; filenames$

If f$<>""   ;cancel or no file was selected if f$ is empty

  If Exists(f$)
  ;  output file to a window
    If ReadFile(0,f$)
      FileInput 0
      While NOT Eof(0)
        i$=3DEdit$(77)
        WPrintScroll:NPrint i$
      Wend

      WPrintScroll:NPrint"***End of file reached.***"

      ;DefaultInput  -- this works only when running from Blitz
      ;              -- or if program is started from a CLI
      ;              -- otherwise there is no default input (CLI)
      ;              -- and your program will crash
      ;              -- just do a Use Window or if none is opened
      ;              -- don't worry about it until
      ;              -- you get to where you need to get some input

    Else
      WPrintScroll:NPrint"file error of some description!"
    EndIf
  Else
    WPrintScroll:NPrint"File did not exist or was empty."
  EndIf

Else
  WPrintScroll:NPrint"No file selected."
EndIf

WPrintScroll:NPrint"Close window to Quit."
ev.l=3D0
While ev<>$200
  ev=3DWaitEvent
Wend

;Free Window 0    Don't need this

;Use Window 0
;If ReadFile(0,"Blitz2:ReleaseNotes")
;  FileInput 0
;EndIf

;MouseWait        Don't need this

WBenchToBack_
End




--BOUNDARY.1748147168.1--




