@NODE "Mail_380" "Re. Getting Keywords"
From: mike.child@sbu.ac.uk
Date: Thu, 29 Oct 1998 13:12:10 +0000
Subject: Re. Getting Keywords


Hello Jamie,

could try playing with this if it helps get you started..

check all my syntax in the manual though because this is off the top of my
head. (eg. should it be Window Input 0 or just Window Input or WindowInput?
can't remember right now just see which one tokenises!) 

WbToScreen 0 ; references to screen 0 now mean WB screen
Window 0,x,y,w,h,$800f,"test",0,0 ; choose your own x,y,w,h and
; check that flag value in the manual!

Window Input 0 ; inkey$ and edit$ work in window 0
Window Output 0 ; print works in window 0

s$=edit$(80) ; user inputs a string up to 80 chr$ long, (must press return)

while len(s$)>0
  i=instr(s$," ") ; find first space
  if i>0
    wd$=left$(s$,i-1) ; first word in wd$
    s$=mid$(s$,i+1) ; strip it from s$
  else
    wd$=s$ ; last word (assuming no trailing space)
  endif
  nprint "word:",wd$,"<" ; just so you can see the words extracted
;check wd$ against your keywords here, store it in a "keywords_in" array 
;or whatever
wend

mousewait
end

Hope this isn't completely useless

Mike Child 


