 If *you're* going to free them, i.e. free them inside your program, 
then you must definately close them before you free them. Otherwise 
you try to free something that isn't closed and all hell breaks 
loose. If you want blitz to do this stuff for you, don't put in code 
for closing or freeing things, but this is a bit untidy.


