@NODE "Mail_394" "Re: screen"
 id 0zPBbl-00071B-00; Fri, 2 Oct 1998 20:15:22 +0000
Date: 02 Oct 98 20:12:02 +0000
From: "Andy Macklin" <andy@toadhall.u-net.com>
Subject: Re: screen
encoding: 7bit
Organization: Badgers Den in The Wild Wood
X-No-Archive: Yes

Andrew typed some of the following:
> I'm having some problems with the "macklin" screen source code.. I can't
> seem to get it to work.. there's a batch of unknown tokens.. and I was
> wondering if anyone can shed any light on this.. 

Sounds like you are either not making amigalibs.res resident (compiler
options) or I have a set of libraries that you don't.

AFAIR the code in question is:

---8<---
FindScreen #Project0Scr  ; Screen 0 is the front screen
*s.Screen= Peek.l(Addr Screen(#Project0Scr))   ; Get system structure of Screen
w.l= *s\NextScreen         ; Get address of next screen
While w.l <> 0              ; Screen exists?
*w.Screen= w.l            ; Put pointer to window address
  If UCase$(Peek.s(*w\Title))=UCase$(pubscr$)
    pubscr$=Peek.s(*w\Title)
    CloseScreen #Project0Scr
    FindScreen #Project0Scr, pubscr$
  End If
  w.l= *w\NextScreen        ; Get address of next screen
Wend
ShowScreen #Project0Scr
--->8--

This shouldn't need more than the basic amigalibs.res. I think.

Andy
--
No dolphins were killed to produce this message.



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_395" "Re: screen"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Sat, 03 Oct 1998 10:45:41 -0500
Subject: Re: screen

Hi Andy

On 02-Oct-98, Andy Macklin wrote:
> Andrew typed some of the following:
>> I'm having some problems with the "macklin" screen source code.. I can't
>> seem to get it to work.. there's a batch of unknown tokens.. and I was
>> wondering if anyone can shed any light on this.. 
> 
> Sounds like you are either not making amigalibs.res resident (compiler
> options) or I have a set of libraries that you don't.
> 

> 
> This shouldn't need more than the basic amigalibs.res. I think.

No, it doesn't need anything but the standard libraries, and the amigalibs.res
file.

But if amigalibs.res is missing, you will get "constant not found" error.

If things don't tokenize, this is a different problem.  Although you both have
the same libraries, the token numbers themselves may be different.  Blitz
source should always be sent to other people saved as ascii, not tokenized
blitz source.
This will avoid the problem.
 

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
