@NODE "Mail_400" "Re: Screen Tags"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Fri, 30 Oct 1998 16:27:23 -0500
Subject: Re: Screen Tags

Warning: This is a message in MIME format. Your mail reader does not
support MIME. Some parts of this message will be readable as plain text.
To see the rest, you will need to upgrade your mail reader.


--BOUNDARY.1747905976.1

Hi Jake

On 29-Oct-98, Jake Frederick wrote:
>    Could someone tell me how to use screen tags or more specifically how to
> use them to scroll a 320*200 display around on a 640*200 bitmap?

Here is an example.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1747905976.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="Autoscroll.asc"



;NEEDS amigalibs.res, WB 2.xx or better

WBStartup

Display.l=69632        ;NTSC lo-res
Oscan.w=1              ;overscan setting - need this!
Dpth.w=3               ;screen depth
Widh.l=640             ;screen width
Heit.l=200             ;screen height

;------- now make the "Program's" screen --------------------

Dim SCRtags.TagItem(11)

SCRtags(0)\ti_Tag=#SA_DisplayID,Display
SCRtags(1)\ti_Tag=#SA_Overscan,Oscan       ;needed or mouse will "wrap around"
SCRtags(2)\ti_Tag=#SA_Depth,Dpth
SCRtags(3)\ti_Tag=#SA_Width,Widh
SCRtags(4)\ti_Tag=#SA_Height,Heit
SCRtags(5)\ti_Tag=#SA_Top,0
SCRtags(6)\ti_Tag=#SA_Left,0
SCRtags(7)\ti_Tag=#SA_AutoScroll,1         ;autoscroll is on!
SCRtags(8)\ti_Tag=#SA_Pens,?DriPens        ;List of 13 Dripens
SCRtags(9)\ti_Tag=#SA_ShowTitle,0
SCRtags(10)\ti_Tag=#TAG_DONE

ScreenTags 0,"Test Screen",& SCRtags(0)    ;open the test screen

Window 0,0,10,300,100,$1000|$8,"Screen info",1,0  ;and a small window

NPrint "Display ",Display
NPrint "Depth=",Dpth
NPrint "Oscan=",Oscan
NPrint "Press close gadget to end"

Window 1,310,10,300,100,$1000,"I'm here!",1,0 ; a second window
NPrint "Hiya!"


Repeat                                     ;just wait until the window
  ev.l=WaitEvent                           ;close gadget is pressed
Until ev=$200

End

Even
DriPens
Dc.w  0,1,1,2,1,3,1,0,2,1,2,1,-1




--BOUNDARY.1747905976.1--




@ENDNODE
