@NODE "Mail_402" "Re: Screen Title Off"
 (envelope-from D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    19 Oct 98 15:09:29 GMT+1
From: "David McMinn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University
Date: Mon, 19 Oct 1998 15:09:15 +0100
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Screen Title Off

On 16 Oct 98, at 20:08, Mathias PARNAUDEAU collapsed under the weight of:

> I just have an easy question for you : in my program, I open a screen,
> display a bitmap (so, the title of the screen disappears). Then, when I
> click on the mouse right button, the title comes in front of the bitmap =
> and I don't want that !
> 
> Any ideas ?

 If you are opening the screen purely to display a bitmap, then you 
should open a backdrop+borderless window and display it inside that, 
as then you can specify the #WFLG_RMBTRAP for your window, which will 
prevent intuition from rendering to your screens bitplanes, if you 
have also opened your screen with type=3D#SCREENQUIET.


|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
