@NODE "Mail_411" "Re: Screens"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Wed, 28 Oct 1998 17:14:01 -0500
Subject: Re: Screens
Encoding: quoted-printable

Hi,

On 28-Oct-98, David McMinn wrote:
> On 28 Oct 98, at 12:21, Stuart Walker floundered in a pit of silicon he=
ll:
> =

>> Does anyone know how to display a picture in hires-laced at 640x512 wi=
th
>> 256 colours (8 bitplanes) on a normal window.
> =

> Here's some code but I don't know if the flags for the screenmode =

> are correct.

Screenmode for PAL hi-res laced is $29004
Or for NTSC hi-res laced use $19004

> =

> WBStartup
> NoCLI
> Screen 0,0,0,640,512,8,$8004,"g",0,1
> LoadBitmap 0,"Space_Station_2:Station2/StationInt",0
> Window 0,0,0,640,512,$100f,"picture",-1,-1
> BitMaptoWindow 0,0
> ShowPalette 0
> Mousewait
> Free BitMap 0
> CloseWindow 0:Free Window 0
> CloseScreen 0:Free Screen 0
> End
> =

> |) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
>  d.mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk ICQ=3D16827694
> =

Later...
-- =

