Hello David,

ńđĺäŕ, 28 Îęň˙áđü 1998, you wrote:

DM>  If *you're* going to free them, i.e. free them inside your program,
DM> then you must definately close them before you free them. Otherwise
DM> you try to free something that isn't closed and all hell breaks
DM> loose. If you want blitz to do this stuff for you, don't put in code
DM> for closing or freeing things, but this is a bit untidy.

Just compile this one and check. It works OK, but there's no
CloseWindow:

findscreen 0
wbtoscreen 0
window 0,0,0,200,100,$e,"",0,1
repeat
 we.l=waitevent
until we=$200
free window 0
end


