Organization: private
Date: 6 Oct 98 20:18:34 +0000
Subject: Shit!
Encoding: 7bit

Hello.

I just had a massive harddrive corruption. My second, but this one's
even worse than the last one.

First of all, it seems that my entire blitz list message-base has
dissappeared. I'm surprised that this internet software is still
essentially intact. It's on it's own partition, but even so I think a
few files have gone (mainly ftp stuff).

I seem to have all my blitz stuff intact from what i can see, thank
god, although I had minor backups of very recent work.

I have about 100 megs of drive space that is so hideously wrecked that
any attemps to repair it causes the harddrive to make horrible,
nightmarish sounds and inflict damage on the other partitions also.
Little bits of sys: are missing, many libraries corrupted, and
typically all my recovery tools were on the partition that
/completely/ dissappeared. Thank god for good old ncomm and bulletin
boards that's what I say! The partition is back now (work:) but there
are many errors.

Just trying to get things in order now.

There was only one thing I wanted to talk of in the past two days and
it was regarding PPC blitz because I was looking a little at getting a
ppc card and blizzardvision. But it's not very likely at the mo.

Anyway, just saying hi, from amidst piles of floppy disks.


-- 
Paul.

