Hi,

>       ok, i`ve been adding lots of features to my new app, and the size of
> the final exe size has increased and increased.... now that it is nearing
> completion i thought i`d re-write some bits, using OS routines instead to
> make the size smaller....  i have also got the NewCommands collection, and i
> looked in there and it said that the ASLRequester blitz lib was around 23Kb,
> so i thought, right thats definately one to replace...

No, the ASLFileRequest command is part of the bbasllib.obj Blitz lib
which is inside "AcidLibs" and it's only 3k. Removing the use of this
lib would cause very little difference in exe size.

Cheers,

-- 
Paul Burkey <--> http://burkey.home.ml.org <-->



