Hi there,

Other people on this list can provide much better information than me about
which libraries take up the most space, but here is another pointer.

Once you have tried everything, use Stonecracker or CrunchMania (both on
Aminet) to crunch your EXE. With the majority of Blitz programmes, it cuts
the file size in half. The difference in load time is negligible because of
the fast processors around nowadays.

Nick / Skillo
