@NODE "Mail_427" "Re: size of exe`s"
From: =?iso-8859-1?Q?Fr=E9d=E9ric?= Laboureur <alphasnd@hol.fr>
Date: Wed, 14 Oct 1998 21:33:47 +0100
Organization: Fantaisie Software
Subject: Re: size of exe`s
Encoding: quoted-printable

    Hi Paul, =


> okay I just did and it was just over 9k difference. So for the sake of
> 6k I agree that is it bigger but once you've written your own
> version of ASLFileRequest$ using OS functions with taglists
> and such you'd end up with something that is only a little bit
> smaller. This is why it's no worth worrying about such a tiny lib.

    Type the program (1 line :-) :

    'a$ =3D ASLFileRequest$("",a$,a$)'

    and compile it with debug off. Say me what size it do.
here it does 24696 bytes.
 =


    Now type this 2 line proggy:

    'NIniteASL
    a$ =3D NASLFileRequest(0)'

    compile it.

Here it does 1448 bytes.

    It's 18 time smaller. Both programs does EXACTELY the same thing.

    But may be we don't have same libs/blitz version...

    =

        Regards,

                        Fred.

