Too bad thats the only proper way of doing it. Its less hassle than the file
stuff. You could also make the program a commodity.. you can trap the
CXUnique event then...


Anyway, here's how to do it the MsgPort way :)


myportname.s = "MyProgramName" ; should be pretty unique

If FindPort(myportname) Then End ; if our port already exists, exit! :)

myport.l = CreateMsgPort(myportname)
If myport=0 Then End ; can't open port?! exit!

 ; your program here

DeleteMsgPort myport


Greetz...



