@NODE "Mail_434" "Re: Stop multiple copies of program running"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Fri, 2 Oct 1998 01:18:46 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Fri, 02 Oct 1998 01:55:38 +0000
Subject: Re: Stop multiple copies of program running

Hi,

> I want to stop multiple copies of my program running at one time.  Whats the
> easiest way for my program to check to see if a copy is already running and
> exit quietly?

You could simply create a MsgPort. This can be done VERY easily
with the RIARexxLibrary (part of Blitz Support Suite) eg:-

If RXCreatePort("UNIQUENAME")=0
  ; Port exists... exit quietly...
Else
  ; Port didn't exist (but it does now!) continue...
EndIf

The same thing could probably be done with the standard Blitz
Arexx/MsgPort commands but I don't have the manual handy. You
can also do it with AmigaOS commands but it's not quite as
simple as the above example.

Cheers,

-- 
Paul Burkey <--> http://burkey.home.ml.org <-->



