@NODE "Mail_452" "Strange Problem - Solution!"
From: Mike Delling <tranquilizer@mike.ruhr.de>
Date: Sun, 04 Oct 1998 16:23:10 +0200
Subject: Strange Problem - Solution!

Hi Blitzers!

I had some problems with my 060 CPU last days. The problem was, that my game
slows down on a 060 cpu and it was much faster on a 030. I tried all! Every
combination of caches on/off, running cyberpatcher, speedychip but it doesn't
matter! 

The command which slows my code down was the Zone command from Reflective
Images.
I wrote a alternative zone statement completely in blitz ans this is much
faster then the zones.obj lib. I'm using a Blizzard 1260-50 with 16 MB ram.
Now my game works fine, hope to complete it this year and release it then into
aminet! 

#THANK YOU ALL FOR YOUR GREAT HELP!!!


-- 

Tranquilizer/ Secretly!
Mike Delling

