@NODE "Mail_457" "Thanks Paul Burkey for Re: problem with EOF registering at all?? (fwd)"
  Mon, 5 Oct 1998 21:47:37 -0700
From: "Rudolf Sanchez" <childrenofsun@email.msn.com>
Subject: Thanks Paul Burkey for Re: problem with EOF registering at all?? (fwd)
Date: Mon, 5 Oct 1998 21:39:11 -0700

Hi Paul,

In your response:

"I usually use:

While Eof(0)=False
   ; read file....
Wend

That works fine. but also "While NOT Eof(0)" works fine too!"

I have as suspicion that Amiga Forever may be the problem as neither
Eof(0)=False or NOT Eof(0) does not seem to work on my setup.  Thus, I will
continue to use:  loc(0)<>lof(0) as it seems to work OK.  However, I made a
note of you statement, as I did not think of that one.

"There was nothing obvious wrong with the source you sent. It seems
to run as expected. The only problem as the file requester which looks
a bit nasty compared to an ASL requester (proportional fonts etc..)."

Thanks, Curt Esser made the same point and definitely looks alot better.

>  If ReadFile(0,f$)
>    FileInput 0
>    While NOT Eof(0)
>    i$=Edit$(77)
>    WPrintScroll:NPrint i$
>    Wend
>  <...snipped...>
>  EndIf

"The above part in particular was working fine. You did forget to close
the file afterwards which could cause problems IF you're doing any
other file access work. So, it's usually best to close files *inside* the
"If ReadFile...EndIf" part since thats the only place th file could be
opened."

Good point and I made a note of it.

Thanks again, Paul Burkey


Rudy
childrenofsun@msn.com







