@NODE "Mail_473" "Value from asm function"
          Paris Thu, 15 Oct 1998 20:33:28 +0200 (MET DST)
          Paris Thu, 15 Oct 1998 20:33:26 +0200 (MET DST)
From: Mathias PARNAUDEAU <Mathias.P@wanadoo.fr>
Date: Wed, 14 Oct 1998 14:51:02 +0100
Subject: Value from asm function
Encoding: quoted-printable

Hi all,

weeks ago, it was discussed about the bad value returned by a function.

It seems it's not necessary to give a parameter. What was forgot is just =
the
function type (.b, .w, .l).

The example was :

Function AlwaysThree{}
   moveq #3,d0
   asmexit
End Function

It gave "0" or ".":-(

If you do that :

Function.b AlwaysThree{}
   moveq #3,d0
   asmexit
End Function

It works ! So, just add the type after the Function word.

Regards,

                                                Mathias

