This would be great but I can't confirm it. But I found a solution that works:
(it's similar to a routine Paul Burkey posted here some months ago):

WBlit to a window that is unable to be seen (eg, 'under' a window)
Instead of using ShowBitmap (I don't have any bitmaps) use

ClipBlit_ RastPort(1),0,0,RastPort(0),0,0,RTGinfo\width,RTGinfo\height,$C0

This copies window 1 (the render window) to the display window.

Works very good - as fast as the blitter!


