@NODE "Mail_481" "Re: What happens ?"
 (envelope-from D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    13 Oct 98 11:14:26 GMT+1
From: "David McMinn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University
Date: Tue, 13 Oct 1998 11:14:18 +0100
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: What happens ?

On 13 Oct 98, at 11:54, Mathias PARNAUDEAU collapsed under the weight of:

> Until there, it's Ok. But when I want to fill this newtype from memory
> (address dress.l for exemple :-) doing 
> 
> *Info\Width=3Dpeek.w(dress.l)                              ok
> *Info\Height=3Dpeek.w(dress.l+2)                         ok
> *Info\Colors=3Dpeek.w(dress.l+4)                        crashes !!!
> *Info\Id=3Dpeek.w(dress.l+6)

 NOOOOOOOOOOOOO, don't do that, its very bad. Currently *Info is a 
Picture type, but it doesn't point to an areay of memory that you own 
(or maybe it does but it isn't to store a Picture type in). The 
reason it crashes is because you are sticking the values from dress+x 
into memory that you should not, such as in the middle of system 
lists, program code, etc, in effect a random address.
 
 First you either need to allocate some memory or point to a Picture 
type variable. The you can change the data all you want.

*Info =3D dress.l works fine because you are now using some memory 
which should be used for that purpose, and it should be quicker than 
the 4 lines as you only have to manipulate 4 bytes rather than all 4 
variables *8 bytes).


|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
