@NODE "Mail_496" "Re: Zoom"
 (envelope-from D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    16 Oct 98 11:43:31 GMT+1
From: "David McMinn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University
Date: Fri, 16 Oct 1998 11:43:18 +0100
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Zoom

On 15 Oct 98, at 16:15, Curt Esser collapsed under the weight of:

> The only other way would be to read the values from the window structure
> itself, but I don't know how to do this.  And you would also need to
> replace these values into the window structure when you re-open, since
> this all disappears when the window is closed down.  

 Its easy to replace the values (use the #WA_Zoom tag), but there 
doesn't seem to be any way of reading this information from the 
window. There may be a #WA_Zoom tag in the ExtData field (pointer to 
array of tags), but I don't think there would be any guarantee that 
the tag would be present.


